


lexical bundles kya ha
ChatGPT
Lexical bundles are sequences of words that commonly appear together in a language. They are also known as "word clusters" or "n-grams" and often include phrases like "in the case of," "as a result of," and "on the other hand." These bundles help in understanding and producing fluent, natural-sounding language.

In Hindi:
Lexical bundles शब्दों के ऐसे समूह होते हैं जो भाषा में अक्सर एक साथ दिखाई देते हैं। इन्हें "word clusters" या "n-grams" भी कहा जाता है। उदाहरण के लिए, "in the case of," "as a result of," और "on the other hand"। ये बंडल्स भाषा को समझने और स्वाभाविक भाषा उत्पन्न करने में मदद करते हैं।

lexical bundles words do
ChatGPT
Sure! Here are some common lexical bundles:

In academic writing:

"In terms of"
"The results of the"
"On the other hand"
"As a result of"
"It is important to"
In everyday conversation:

"At the end of the day"
"You know what I mean"
"Do you want to"
"I don't know"
"A lot of"
In Hindi:
कुछ सामान्य lexical bundles निम्नलिखित हैं:

शैक्षिक लेखन में:

"In terms of" (के संदर्भ में)
"The results of the" (के परिणाम)
"On the other hand" (दूसरी ओर)
"As a result of" (के परिणामस्वरूप)
"It is important to" (यह महत्वपूर्ण है)
दैनिक बातचीत में:

"At the end of the day" (दिन के अंत में)
"You know what I mean" (आप समझते हैं मेरा मतलब)
"Do you want to" (क्या आप चाहते हैं)
"I don't know" (मुझे नहीं पता)
"A lot of" (बहुत सारे)
